          <Comment>This variant is also known as p.Pro1411Profs Ter298. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 587424). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This premature translational stop signal has been observed in individual(s) with epidermolysis bullosa dystrophica (PMID: 27899325). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Gly1412Aspfs*298) in the COL7A1 gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in COL7A1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 16971478). This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency).</Comment>
